<br>
While I tend to agree with the final statement here, I've hit monsters halfway embedded in a wall before with thrown weapons and arrows, I don't believe that first part to be true.  I also have not needed gigantic open spaces either, just a clear shot.  Sometimes that can be a bit tough to get with crowds around things and no high ground, however.  Of course, I play a Warrior not a Ranger, maybe the rules are different for them... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/18/02 6:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: +26000 damage to CT via a BOW???</span><hr size=1> Bit of info on ranger skills...<br>
<br>
pre 51 rangers do the same dmg with archery that anyone else would do with a similar bow and similar skill.  The only differences were...<br>
<br>
Rangers can crit on archery hits.<br>
<br>
Hybrids can only get 75 skill in archery<br>
<br>
Used to be rangers got better bows than anyone else via <br>
questing back in the old world, but DN bows are usable by warriors and rogues who can get 200 skill in archery pre 51 though they are expensive.  At the very high end there are some uber ranger only bows now though.<br>
<br>
Then at 51 ranger gain double dmg on all bow hits on mobs that are not rooted or moving (basicly someone has to be tanking it)<br>
<br>
Then at 55 they get the trueshot disc which lets them do double dmg with archery for 2 minutes.  Refresh time is 72 minutes.<br>
<br>
Via AA skills at 59+ they can get the following...<br>
<br>
Endless quiver- Ranger needs 1 arrow of any type that will be used every time they fire but never get  used up.  This is important not just as a matter of convenience because prior to getting this skill the ranger will commonly be using crappy 3 dmg arrows that they can summon via their kunark class armor bracer (tolans) After obtaining this skill they can basicly use the best fletched arrows (10dmg + 4 bane dmg (band dmg on arrows is supposedly broken) all the time which would be far to expensive over time to even consider for regular use.<br>
<br>
Archery Mastery- Double dmg on all archery, functional all the time. Stacks with trueshot and the 51 bonus.<br>
<br>
Combat fury- Gives rangers the ability to crit on normal melee and increases the frequency of bow crits.<br>
<br>
Limitiations of Archery.<br>
<br>
Can't be used in tight spaces.  You will get the &quot;you are too close&quot; msg.<br>
<br>
People can get between you and the mob blocking the shot.<br>
<br>
If some portion of the mob is in the wall the arrows will poof because it believes you are trying to shoot the mob through the wall.  This can be countered by lining yourself up exactly along the wall that the mob is touching supposing this is feasable.  This is because when a wall is parellel to the invisible line that is drawn between you and a mob the game doesn't do collision detection to find out if the wall is in the way because logicly it can't be.<br>
<br>
Slopes can cause you to get the too high too low msg even when you have a clear view of the mob.<br>
<br>
Archery is slowed down by lag.  Because it is based on you hitting a button for each shot and sending a msg to the server each time lag results in fewer shots per minute.<br>
<br>
A NOTE ABOUT MELEE DMG IN GENERAL<br>
<br>
Melee dmg is very erratic, much more so than nuke dmg.  With warrior melee dmg your looking at misses (33%), double attack rolls (66% success) , duel wield rolls (66% success), as well as the dmg roll for any given attack which is much more evenly distributed along the range than a nuke is the average over time falls abouthalfway between max and min I believe.  But what if you get a lot of good rolls or a lot of awful ones?  It gives you a bad view of warrior dmg for good or ill unless you take a longer view.<br>
<br>
Thus dmg over a short period of time is very very very unreliable because its just a matter of what rolls succeeded.  Aside from the fact that EQs semi random number generator is supposed to be prone to streaks of good and bad luck (no random number generator is really random its just a computer program with a seed known only to verant).<br>
<br>
Trueshot logs are by nature short term logs (duh) and you must also consider the bragging rights factor.  People will post the logs in which they got good rolls and delete the ones in which they hit for ones a lot.<br>
<br>
To properly evaluate trueshot + aa skills you need to take the average dmg of a long period of time with all archery aa skills maxed with good gear/buffs.  Then consider a range of fights of varrying duration and double the dmg for the 2 minute period in which trueshot is active. For example if AA archery dmg = 90 dps (not unreasonable at the high end) then a break down would look like this.<br>
<br>
2  minute fight average dps 180 dmg done 21600<br>
3  minute fight average dps 150 dmg done 27000<br>
4  minute fight average dps 135 dmg done 32400<br>
10 minute fight average dps 108 dmg done 64800<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
